critical_positive: I felt we were both friendly, open and intelligent, sharing similar concerns about the state of the world. Because neither of us was afraid to express an opinion early in the conversation, it was easy to talk about various topics. And with little shyness or apprehension, we were able to explore those topics more deeply, in a short time frame, than would the average strangers. The intelligence I perceived in my partner also drew me deeper into his opinions of the topics we discussed.
critical_negative: There was a slight video lag, but it only caused one or two hiccups that I can recall, which caused us both to pause and say, "Go ahead," to one another. In that instance, we both politely waited for one another and one or the other of us - I don't recall which - took the initiative rather quickly and began speaking again. Otherwise, I felt everything worked well.

rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will be very good and positive. It will be productive and I will accomplish some of the goals that I have laid out for myself. I believe that this week could be a turning point in my life, wherein I am able to make some big changes.
critical_positive: We had quite a few topics in common to talk about. My partner was aware of world politics and kind enough to express his feelings in a moderate non-offensive manner. He was curious and was a good listener, he was also very forthcoming and always had a smile on his face.
critical_negative: I think at some point my conversation partner tried to get a little personal and that was uncomfortable. Also, I think speaking about politics was a little bit difficult as I wasn't sure what his personal views were. Lastly, I think my partner tried to ask me about my future plans which made me uneasy.
